      <div class="truncate-300 clearfix" data-truncate="300">
      <h1 class="single__heading single-post__heading">Charging up</h1>
<h2 class="single__subheading single-post__subheading">Electric vehicle infrastructure buildout gathers power</h2>
<p class="single__published single-post__published"><span class="published"><span class="published__date"><span class="published__date-label">PUBLISHED<span> </span></span><span class="published__datetime-date">AUGUST 29, 2022</span></span></span></p>
<p class="single__published single-post__published"><span class="published"><span class="published__author"><span class="published__author-label">BY<span> </span></span><a class="published__author-name" rel="author" href="https://www.virginiabusiness.com/byline/mason-adams/">MASON ADAMS</a></span></span></p>
<p class="single__published single-post__published"><span class="published">Sullivan and Sen. Dave Marsden, D-Fairfax, co-sponsored legislation this year to establish a transportation decarbonization program to disburse up to $20 million annually in grants for private developers to install EV charging stations, covering 50% of nonutility costs in most localities and 70% in economically disadvantaged communities.</span></p>
<p class="single__published single-post__published"><span class="published">https://www.virginiabusiness.com/article/charging-up/</span></p></div>

