      <div class="truncate-300 clearfix" data-truncate="300">
      <h2 class="entry-sub-title font-sans text-gray-400 font-normal text-18 sm:text-22 leading-23 sm:leading-27 mb-15">Legislation results from collaboration between senator, state trucking association</h2>
<div class="entry-meta flex text-12 leading-30 mb-20">
<div class="entry-author-meta flex font-semibold">
<a class="inline-block mr-7" rel="author" href="https://www.freightwaves.com/news/author/nickaustin"><img class="avatar avatar-30 photo w-30 h-30 rounded-full bg-gray" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4c7867668184a5b4d2af5d1816759671?s=30&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g" alt="" width="30" height="30"></a><span class="meta-author inline-block mr-5"><a class="text-gray hover:text-blue" href="https://www.freightwaves.com/news/author/nickaustin">Nick Austin</a></span><a class="text-gray hover:text-blue" rel="author noopener" href="https://twitter.com/FreightWeather" target="_blank"><em class="tie-icon-twitter"></em></a>
</div>
<span class="mx-10 text-30 text-gray-100 leading-27">·</span>Monday, February 28, 2022</div>
<figure class="post-thumbnail relative"><img class="w-full h-auto wp-post-image wp-post-image" src="https://www.freightwaves.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/VA-law-story_1-1200x675.jpg" alt="" width="1200" height="675"></figure>
<p><span>Democratic Sen. Dave Marsden, the main architect of the bill, introduced it in late January, and </span><a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://lis.virginia.gov/cgi-bin/legp604.exe?221+sum+SB706" target="_blank">it passed in the state Senate less than a month later by a vote of 26-13</a><span>. It could become law as early as July 1 if it passes in the House of Delegates and the governor signs it.</span></p>
<p><span>https://www.freightwaves.com/news/keep-right-virginia-bill-outlines-winter-storm-lane-restriction-for-truckers</span></p></div>

